betterquesting:10.desc:8:
§b这里的任务大多数都很人性化，例如：鹤嘴锄任务中，你可以选择制作一把铲子和一把手斧来完成任务。

§b所有匠魂任务都可以在最后的需求分页里打勾完成。

§r当工具耐久耗尽时，你需要在工具装配台中，使用与工具头部相同的材料来修复它，或者你也可以将磨制工具与工具合成来修复。

当你把模具箱放置在模具加工台和部件加工台之间时，它们会自动相连并拥有更方便的功能。

将空白模具放置在模具加工台中就能制作工具模具。制作好的模具放入部件加工台中，再放上可用材料（比如木头）就能够制作工具部件。最后在工具装配台中将工具部件组装，即可获得一把完整的工具。

所需的工具部件材料是任意的，任务都会完成。(或一把完整的镐)
制作一把鹤嘴锄或铲+斧。任意材料都可以完成任务。

§b任意部件都可以完成任务，你可以在匠魂提供的基础剑类武器中任选制作。§r

燧石、骨头和仙人掌很适合前期用来制作武器部件。书中能看到所有可用的部件材料。

这些材料能够强化你的武器！

交错次元十分令人讨厌。完成任务来避免进入那可怕的地方。

你仍然需要制作护身符来完成任务以继续发展。
Standard gathering routine.
Used for more advanced machinery.

前期的余烬！
任意手里拿着工匠单片眼镜即可看到不同方块的工作方式。

带着大气能量测量表能够找到余烬能量富集的地方，这里最适合放置你的晶体开采机了。

没有gui意味着你很难知道机器内部发生了什么，所以制作一些物品计量表吧！


查阅古代法典能够看到更详细的物品信息，是的，比任务描述详细。
这儿有一些东西帮助你搭建物流系统。

将方块放置在基岩上方三格以内，然后用管道将煤炭等可燃物从上方的洞抽入进开采机内，它就会开始开采灰烬晶体！开采机大小为3X3。

在顶部中心处放置机械核心连接器（或机械核心）可增加多个访问面。

§c如果使用的是机械核心连接器，你必须右键放置，如果潜行右键放置，它就不会连接到开采机上！

如何使用：

放置任意方块，然后在顶上放置压缩空间机械制作器，将它朝向你想要压缩投影存在的地方放置。右键制作器来查看另外三个制作器可放置的位置。右键另一个制作器来查看另外两个制作器需要放置的位置。请确保每个制作器面向同一个点，且地板是平整的。

如果放置正确，一个§e§6橙色的全息投影§r会在中心生成。这儿就是你需要搭建配方的地方。

最基础的一点，制作器最少也要离地一格方块。
使用灵魂瓶，制作新物品。
想要自动化这家伙好像有些难办。你需要找到一种方法来放置充能方块，同样的，你也需要找到破坏和收集未充能方块的方法。
魔法很有趣！

使用金属来升级你的装备。

将冶炼炉放在装有熔岩的焦黑储罐上。放入2个金或粘土，融化后，右键放置在冶炼炉上的浇注口来将熔融金属排出，你可以将其排出到浇筑台上，配合各种铸模即可制作金属制对应物品。

§c冶炼炉只能同时容纳一种流体！§r

§b徽章可以在商店任务章节里兑换资源。

§5等级6的种子能够以1比2的比例向下分解。请明智地选择！
搭建冶炼炉的第一步。你需要比任务需求更多的焦黑砖，但目前来讲，这些足够了。
铸模成型后，往里导入熔融金属。这个任务需要铁来完成。
由巨型激光供能，这个多方块机器能够将一些极稀有、极珍贵的材料煅烧在一起。

在制作器中间的橙色投影中，按照配方搭建多方块结构，然后将催化物品扔到投影中。

你可以把它用在晶体开采机上，它同样能够增加开采机的可交互面。
需要2000度高温。
用来制作板或致密板。

将物品从容器内抽出，并传输到管道尽头。 

§c提取泵需要红石信号激活。

用工匠单片眼镜查看它的顶部和底部，你可以发现底部是用来输入固态余烬，顶部是用来输出余烬能量的。在顶部放上灰烬能量发射器即可传输能量，然后在铜质灰烬能量单元或灰烬能量驱动的机器上放置一个灰烬能量接收器即可接收能量。

用工匠锤在接收器处§6潜行右键§r，然后在发射器处§6右键§r。为发射器提供一个§6红石信号§r后，你就能看到灰烬能量被传输出来！灰烬能量最大发射距离为25格。

§b在前期，灰烬能量可以用来代替少量RF，你只需在机器上放置一个接收器！

betterquesting:10.name:8: 使用灰烬能量冶炼金属（2倍矿物）
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
在熔炼炉正确一侧放上灰烬能量接收器。用锤子潜行右键接收器，然后右键发射器即可将它们连接在一起。使用拉杆来激活发射器。

你可以拿着物品右键熔炼炉将物品放进去，也可以直接把物品扔进去，当然，用管道抽进去也是可行的。 

这是前期矿物双倍化的方法之一。
用这些东西对着泵右键。在你获取电弧炉之前，你无法制作铝。

与物品管道的工作方式相同。 

§c§c请确保有红石信号用来激活提取器。

Fluid goes in the Bottom, one empty block, then the Stamper above that. Right click with the stamp to attach, them power with Ember.

Be sure that your Ember Shards are placed before you start piping metal in!

Items are collected in a Bin below the Stamp Base, or dropped if there is no Bin.
Cast out one of the five basic alloys to complete this chapter!

Welcome to Multiblock Madness! 

Most vanilla recipes are unchanged, so you can start at your own pace. Take you time setting up a base, or rush ahead with progression.

Recipes get progressively more expensive as you go through the pack, so stock up!

This is basically a hand held book shelf. Craft it together with any book to add it.

Right click with it to open the book menu, then once you are done looking at whichever book just left click the air with it.

§bThe filled Tome is craftable, so if you do lose your Tome, just craft another.

You will need to go to the Betweenlands before you can craft your first backpack, the Lurker Skin Pouch.

In the meantime, have a Shulker box!

Right click with the Chisel to open the block chisel menu, then put something that can be chiseled, for example cobblestone. Then you click a variant to chisel all the cobble in the upper left slot into the one you picked. You can also leave a chiseled block in the slot, which will enable you to chisel inworld blocks of the same type with left click.

§d§rWe have a few very useful hotkeys to set up in this pack:

§2Better Questing: Opens the questbook.

§bOre Excavator: Holding down while using a tool will cause connected blocks to be harversted as well.

§eNotes: Opens a notepad.

§6Find Me: Pushing while hovering oven an item will cause nearby chests containing that item to light up.



§rIf you are having trouble with a quest, read the discription!

When you see a red X§r, you will need to check it to complete the quest.
This pump needs a small amount of power in the top to run, as well as a redstone signal. Right click a side with the Hammer to change in/output.

Shift right click on each corner of a 3D craft, then place the Markers inside the Replicator. Link the last Marker to where you want the Builder to assemble the structure.

After receiving RF and the items, it will start to build.
Place one of these as a pipe, then right click it with the only thing you want to pass through it.
Upgrade a Gas Pump by right clicking with a Compressing Unit.

Can be placed in the body Bauble slot, and opened with a hotkey.

§bYou may notice a lot of single use crafted quests, such as this one, giving a choice for another of the same item. This is intended for players on a team.

Place the §5Flux Condenser§r on top of one of the jars, with the other four connected by tube to it. Then place the Lattices on top, all connected to the Condenser as well. 

Each of the outside jars will need to be filled with Essenta to activate the §5Condenser§r. Be sure to keep the Lattces clean by using a Filter on them when they get clogged.

Hold paper in your hand, and Charcoal in your off hand, then shift right click your Waystone to copy the strange symbols. This also requires a small amount of XP to create.





(or you can use the /home command, but thats not as cool)

Stores MORE fluid!

Place the Valve on top of the Reservoir. Fluid can be transfered through any of the sides or the bottom.

Place any tool or weapon in the center of the tool station along with a part to replace that part.

§bAdd these to your pickaxe for more specific Fossil drops.
When you melt an ore, some impurities are lost. If you attach this to the base of the melter when you melt down some ores, you can collect a second molten metal type.

Assemble a 4x4 base, then place 2 exterior layers, so you have a 2x2 open interior.

You have two options for heating: Advanced Solar Panels on each 4 corners (these need to be inset one block.)

Or you can use Heaters placed adjacent to a valve. §c§rRemember to set the RF useage in the machine!

Simply by supplying this with a steady source of water, you can increase your ember burning efficiency by 1.5. If you place it on a block of metal, then heat it up by surounding it with lava or fire, you can double that.

§bTry placing this on a block of Dawnstone!

Place the Mechanical Core on top of the Bore, then attach the Mechanical Actuator to it. Next connect it with axels to your Steam Engine. 

Dont forget to add a gear!

This handy device allows you to store xp.

§bThe Rod is required to store XP on a server.
Finding things is a challenge sometimes.

Picked as a flower in the overworld, or mined deep underground.

Magic Crystals have many uses in Wizardry
Who likes constantly going back underground?
Anyone standing next to the flower will find their xp being turned in mana.

Mechanical Power can be used instead of ember to greatly increase efficiency from some of your ember machines. The Ember Bore and Pump are the most effected by switching to mechanical power.

The steam engine can either have coal and water piped into it, or steam. Piping in steam produces much more energy.

Axles go between the Steam engine output and the Gearbox, which has the input facing you when you place it. 

The Gearbox needs a gear on any face with an Axle to complete the connection.

Whenever you make a right turn with an Axle, you willl need a Gearbox there.

§6Dawnstone Gears are the fastest.

Make a 3x3x3 cube, then hammer the front with your hammer.

Coal goes in, Coke Coal and Creosote Oil comes out.

Can also be used to create Charcoal.
This can be used to hide Conduits.
Place Scrap/boxes inside for UU Matter.
These gears can handle the greatest speeds.
Look up the recipe for molten Dawnstone to create.

Assemble a hollow 3x3x3 cube, then place the controller in the center of one of the layers. The drain can go anywere, but put it on the second row up, then attach the faucet to it. Place the table below the faucet.

§6You can increase the capacity by adding extra middle layers.

§rThe High Oven works by burning Coke Coal to produce heat. Once the heat is high enough, it well start the melting process. If it is hot enough, and you have the correct inputs, it can also create a few alloys.

Picking up an ingot will complete the quest.

Place iron, sand (or Limestone Flux), and sulfur in the High Oven, then wait for the temperature to rise enough for the iron to melt.

§cMake sure it is hot enough before trying to craft alloys!

§rIf you use iron ore instead of iron ingots, you will get two steel per ore.
You will need 3,172 Coils to get to the correct size.

The Blast Furnace is simpler, so it might be worth investing in, but the High Oven is much more efficient.


Build a 3x3x3 cube, with the Hopper goes on top, then hammer the front. Pre-Heaters are placed on each side as an optional upgrade, and are powered from the top.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Making your way to the Betweenlands
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Either find a swamp and kill lots of Dark Druids until you get all the Talisman pieces, or you can craft them.

§cYou will need to craft the Talisman on a Dark Druid Altar!

§rOnce you have the Swamp Talisman, use it on a sapling centered on a 17x17 flat area to create the portal.
Right click with a wrench to toggle auto output, press M while holding to toggle bucket mode.

This is used to visulize some multiblock structures in JEI. 

Shouldn't have to say this, but don't actually do one of these crafts!
You can place either rings or more valves on top to increase the amount of fluid it can hold by 40 buckets each.

Unlock Alchemy all the way to Advanced Essenta Transport.

Also unlocks Hedge Alchemy.

§bUnneeded if skipping research, or if you plan on doing all of it by hand.

Right click to enter THE BENEATH.

Once you enter, look for the giant cavern.

This is great place to run Pumpjacks and the Excavator!
Found as lakes in the huge cavern in The Beneath.
Where these two liquids touch, sand is created, with a §bvery§r small chance of Aquamarine.
This is enough to build the smallest size tank, a 3x3x3 cube. The frame must be made out of Dynamic Tanks, and Glass or Valves can go on the faces.

Drop the correct petals, then some seeds into a filled Petal Apothecary.

Placing the correct blocks around the Pure Daisy will slowly transform them.

§bCheck out what other blocks can be transformed!
§r

The §aMunchdew§r will eat leaves in an area around itself as long as possible, then take a break when it runs out or fills up. Each leaf eaten will generate some amount of §3§1§9Mana§r.

§3

This hammer is mainly used to complete the multiblock structures from Immersive Engineering.

§bPlacing the tank into the Coke Oven will fill it with oil.
Place this anywhere on the structure.

§b§rLeft click to change modes, then right click to place whatever item you want processed. The Profiling Bench does not need power.

Items can be piped in and out quite simply, so don't hesitate to set up a small automation for it!

Rockhounding can be an intimadating mod! However in this pack it is §r§6almost §6completely optional§r, with the exception of this, the Metal Alloyer in Chapter 5, and the Vapor Distilation Chamber in Chapter 7. It is highly recommended to do at least the next quest in the line, to familiarize yourself with some of the concepts.

The Rockhounding questbook chapter will explain in depth how to get the most out of it, and if you need further help, feel free to stop by our §9Discord§r!

betterquesting:10.name:8: Intro to Rockhounding: The Mineral Sizer (2x Ore)
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Simple ore doubling, as well as the start of 8x ore processing!

Assemble these as shown in the guide book you got in the previous quest, under §6Structures and Machines > Tier 2 Machines > Mineral Sizer.§r

Each Machine you assemble will need a §4Power Station§r, with Fuel and/or RF. Looking at which icons are blue on the top of the power station GUI will tell you which is needed. Fuel can be either §6Lava§r, §7Syngas§r, or any burnable item. §c(This one needs fuel)§r


Place 8 of any type §bCrushing Gears§r in the tanks, then crush your ore at the correct level in the Sizer Controller. You will need to remove the result from the Gangue Collecter before you can start the next batch. 

The §f§eServer§r is optional in any multiblock that includes one, so we can ignore it for now.


§cOne thing to note is that some of these machines do not perform well on a server, so it is recomended to use Compact Machines for your processing chain.

Crush Coal or Charcol blocks in the Crushing Tank at level 2 to get Cracked Coal.

Pipe the Cracked Coal and water into the Slurry Pond. Having more then one of these would be a good idea.

Pipe the Coal Slurry into the Cistern, and fill the top of the Burner with Water.

You will need a lot of lava to bring the heat up initially.

A Gas Holder can be used in place of the Vessel in any of these multiblocks, and can hold 1,000 times the amount.

§bMaking two extra of these machines might come in handy later.

You can use the same tank for input as the output for Raw Syngas. If you choose not to, you will need an additional gas tank.

Pipe the Syngas into any Power Station that requires fuel.

Activate the Gas Pump by shift right clicking it with an empty hand.

§bMaking an extra one of these Machines might come in handy.
§1test§2test§3test§4test§5test§6test§7test§8test§a§9test§9§atest§btest§ctest§dtest§etest§ftest§ktest§l§8§l§rtest§a§ktest
Your first Obsidian.

Place this one block above the Obsidian, place the block of choice between the two, then supply with redstone.

This is mostly used for crushing stone smaller and smaller.

Place the pump over a water source block and supply redstone to the back. It has a chance to consume the source block over time.

Pipe water into the Evaporation Tank, wait, then pipe raw salt to the seasoning rack.

This is a slow process, and weather and biome will have an effect on how long it takes. It is advised to have multiple tanks evaporating at once.
Drop petals in here, along with some seeds, to craft your first magical flower, the Pure Daisy.
Right click with a petal on the grass, use regular bonemeal on it, then shear it down.
Aim your Mana Spreader at the pool and watch it fill up! Very slowly.

Place Greatwood around the Pure Daisy, and watch the sparkles.

Place Mossy Cobble around the Pure Daisy, and watch the sparkles.

§bDrop Grass and Cobble in water for Mossy.
Mana Spreaders are mainly used to transport the mana from collecting fVis/Fluxlowers to the Mana Pool.

Place diagonally to a 3x3 pool of water for best effect.

No need to automate, very low mana generation.

§cWill decay over one Hour!

Feed this one any fuel source.

§bHint: Look into an auto dropper above a pressure plate for automating.

§cWill decay over one Hour!

Place lava diagonally to this flower, but dont let it touch!

Tricky to automate, high mana generation. Requires a cool down after consuming a lava source, during which any lava consumed will not produce mana.

Shift-right click with the §2Wand of the Forest§r between generating flowers and the Mana Spreader, and the Mana Spreader and the Mana Pool.
If you place the Mana Spreader first, the flowers will be linked already.

Shift-right click air to change modes.

Place your Wand in the Arcane Workbench to add spells and recharge with Magic Crystals.

Explore dungeons and talk to Wizards to get better gear.
This is where you modify your Wands and add spells.

Throw this on various things to activate their true magical potential!

§U§cYou will need to use the Thaumonomicon to guide your way through this mod! §f

Use the quest chapter to get familiar with some of the concepts.

Use this on everything you can to learn more about the magical world around you.

It also comes with a handy Vis/Flux meter on the top left.

§bShift right clicking on chests might be a good way to rack up some knowledge.

Collect a bunch of those glowing crystals you've found growing around underground! 

They will spread over time if you aren't crafting too many arcane things in the area.

Your first arcane crafts will be here.

After learning how to make an Arcane Workbench in your Thaumonomicon, simply throw some more §dSalis Mundus§r on a plain old crafting table.
Place your wand in the center of the table, then place a spell in one of the five slots around it. Press the check mark to save your changes.
Octine Ore is one of the base crafting materials for many items in the Betweenlands, its also hot enough to craft the High Oven with.
Sulfur is the main fuel source in the Betweenlands, and if you crush it up, it is one of the main components in making your first steel.

Life Crystals are primarily used to power the Animator, but can also be used to automate the Mortar and Infuser.

They can be recharged with Wight's Hearts.
Use this deep underground, and follow the sound to find an underwater Life Crystal Stalactite or muddy Middle Gem.

Mainly used to repair tools.
Check JEI for what you can craft with this.
A basic magic building block.
Place the Pestle in the Mortar, then some sulfur. Left click to crush it down into High Oven usable sulfur.
Find a Swamp and kill some Dark Druids hanging out ominously.

Use the Sky Compass to find fallen Meteorites. Hidden deep inside will be a chest, with a press in it.
You will need to collect all four.

Place the item shown in JEI inside the Inscriber, along with the approprate press. 

Inscribers can be run with RF or AE power.
These are used in a great many things in this mod.

This one will eat leaves to make mana.

§bTry the Forester!

Welcome to the start of Applied Energistics! You can build a storage system without the Controller and no Interfaces untill you unlock §bPlatinum§r.

Place some Certus Quartz inside a powered Charger, and wait till it sparkles. Also found rarly underground.

This can only be powered from the top and bottom, but items can be piped in and out from any side.
Crush up some Quartz or Fluix, mix it with sand, then drop in water for about 24 hours.
Throw the Nether Quartz, Redstone, and Charged Certus Quartz into a pool of water.
Place these around a water block, connect them to your network to give them power, then throw your seeds in.
Place your seeds inside here for the best growing speed. You can also create Fluix with this machine.
Feel free to upgrade to 4k or higher as soon as possible.
AE will only accept its own power, and one way to do that is by converting it through this.

Build a hollow cube, at least 3x3x3. The Controller goes bottom center, the middle layer can be glass, and the drain can go anywhere.

Pipe or bucket fluids in or out of the drain.

This is great for storing all your fluids.
The ME Drive holds 10 Drives.
These can be crafted into storage discs, or used in crafting CPU's.

Place your Crafting Storage connected to your network, then the Molecular Assembler next to a Interface, also connected to your network. 

Next place your incoded pattern into the Interface. 

If you go back to your terminial, you should be able to request your item to be crafted.
The Basic Terminal is used to access all of your stored items. Hook it up with a cable to your network.
Craft items from your storage with the built in 3x3 crafting table.
Access your stored fluid from here.
You can also use the Energy Acceptor to make a coal generator instead.

The Pattern Terminal is where you create encoded Patterns, and the Interface Terminal allows you to access all of your ME Interfaces at once.

Place your Blank Pattern inside your Pattern Termnial, then open a recipe in jei. Press the plus icon to copy it to the terminal, then press the arrow to encode the pattern.
A much improved version of the Inscriber.
This very happy potato will be more then happy to be your companion!

How the Network interacts with other blocks.

The Interface has countless uses, but it is primarly used in autocrafting.

Running out of channels yet? 

The ME Controller can handle up to 32 channels per face, as well as function as an Energy Acceptor.
This is one of the biggest quality of life upgrades since the ME Controller!

These are the basic cables that can connect your network.

You can use Cable Anchors to separate adjacent cables.
Place any combination of either of these blocks, plus at least one Crafting Storage, in a rectangular shape to create a Crafting Processing Unit.

Smart Cables have the same functionality as the fluix ones, but have the added use of displaying the amount of channels, or network blocks, connected to your network.

Dense Cables can carry 32 channels, instead of the 8 that the other two types can handle.
Place these inside the wireless access point.

Place this in the bottom slot of your security terminal, program it for access, then have them shift right click with it to lock it to them. 

Next just put it in the storage area of the Security Terminal.

These have a bit of a learning curve, but stick with it and your network capacity will explode.

P2P Tunnels come in pairs, normally. The output end will be toward your machines, and the input end is towards your controller. 

Once you place a pair of P2P's, shift right click with the Memory Card on the input, then right click on your output end to link them.

Channels go in and out the wide ends, and the smaller ends just need to be connected to your network like any other network block.



Shift right click to clear your Memory Card.
Place the Storage Bus against any storage to have the network recognize it.
Some useful items to have.

Throw the §dSalis Mundus§r on the Caldron to turn it into a Crucible. Fill with water, then heat.

This can be a messy process, with wasted Essenta converting into §5Flux§r and polluting the atmosphere. This can cause §5Void Rifts§r, which can destroy blocks if left unattended. Look in the top left corner of the screen while holding the §6Thaumometer§r to check your Vis/Flux levels. The Dark Purple is how much §5Flux§r is in the chunk.

Use §bQuartz Slivers§r to clean up after a craft, but make sure to unlock the research first!

This will be used to make Brass until you get access to Zinc.

Right click on the top of the Crucible or drop items in.

This can be used as a light source, or to heat your Crucible.

§cThe Thaumometer can not see what is inside, you need the goggles for that. Don't drop it in!

The sand and coal are all you'll need to be able to craft this.

Alumentum burns four times longer then regular coal, and can be thrown to cause a small explosion.

§bCan also be used as High Oven and Blast Furnace fuel to great effect.

A key step in metal processing.

Right click on the tank with the Mod Wrench until it shows purging Brine. Then all you need to do is pipe the Brine into a tank for storage.
Heating up already hot metal to create an infernally hot ingot.
With Nature's Compass you can choose a biome, and it will point to the closest one.
Osmium is found in the Beneath

§d§5Raw Voidstone§r is found in the Beneath.

Items can be piped in and out for basic automation.

Right click anywhere with the §4Inspectoris Scandalum§r to set the Tier, then shift-right click on your altar to show a holographic layout in order to upgrade to that tier.

You might need a head for the dagger, one option is to place a piece of obsidian along with an ender pearl on a tinkers sword to give it beheading.

Using the §bSacrificial Dagger§r next to the altar will damage you to fill your altar by a small amount, while hitting mobs next to an altar with the §bDagger of Sacrifice§r will insta-kill them for some blood.
Once you have some oil, you can make the Small Storage Crate, or if you have already gotten some void crystals you can create the medium variety.

Place §6§r8§r of any type of rune in a ring one level below your blood altar to upgrade it to level 2.

These are the basic runes, they can be upgraded to modify your Blood Altar in diferent ways.

You'll need a lot of §eSlate Dust§r coming up soon, so set up automation for it as soon as you can.

Now that you have some blank runes, you can go ahead and craft the Runic Matrix!

§bClaiming this quest will unlock the research for Infusion.
Inside the Fluidpedia, use the Ampoule on whichever fluid you want to be filtered, then you can use it to set the filters in the next quest.

Assemble this as shown in the guide book, then set the filters in the fluid input as shown in JEI to create Sodium Hydroxide.

Pipe the Saturated Brine and Water into the fluid input. Start the process in the Electrochemical CSTR.

If you've done everything correctly, Sodium Hydroxide should start outputting on the bottom.

The Power Station needs RF and Fuel.
Magical Dust?

Items go in the top, and the controls are on the bottom.

Each of the items will need to be blended for the next step.

The Power Station needs RF.

Rock Crushing machines might be your best bet here.

Assemble the Lab Oven as shown in the guide book. It is highly recomended to set up a separate Lab Oven to process each of the upcoming products.


To set up automation with a Server, place the Server File in the center slot and scroll to the desired recipe with the arrows. Next chose if you want it repetable or not and how many times it should run. Then place it in the top row and active the server. The Lab Oven will then run the recipes defined by the Server Files in order once you activate it.

Assemble another Gas Purifier with an Air Compresser pumping air into the input.

You won't need the Particulate Collector for purifying air.

The Power Station and Air Compresser will both need to be powered with Syngas.

You will need input and output tanks as well.

Power the Station with RF.

Use Cryogenic Distilation to seperate air into its various components.

You will need 2 gas tanks, one for each of the separated gases.

The Gas Bulb will be your output for rare gases, push the eject icon to allow piping them out.

§I§cIf you are playing on a server, be sure to house this machine inside a compact machine.
Grab a bucket of Sodium Hydroxide to complete.
Requires Sulfuric Acid, Water, and Chloride Bearing Compound.
Requires Sulfuric Acid and Fluorite Bearing Compound.
Swapping your Gold Cataylsts out with Platinum ones will double your output of Nitric Acid.
Pipe Fly Ash into your Precipitation Chamber, along with Hydrochloric Acid. Then pipe the result along with water into a Lab Oven.

Highly recomended to set up the Catalyst Regenerator under this machine.

Also requires 4 gas tanks.

Use this to create Ammonia, then assemble a second one to process some of that into Nitric Acid.

Power with RF.
You will need a LOT of Liquid Ammonia, so the next few quests will give you a few more options on how to get more.

It's recomended here to assemble another Reforming Reactor to process Nitric Acid.

Requires Ammonia and Oxygen.

Use this to convert Ammonia Gas to its liquid form.

Also requires a Vessel/Holder, and a fuel supplied Power Station.

Place this under any machine that works with catalysts, pipe Flue Gas into the tank and supply with water. 

Once you turn it on it will pull catalysts out for repair and put them back.

This quest tangent will show you how to recycle Toxic Waste into Flue Gas, which will allow you to save on §6rare §rmaterials by repairing Catalysts.

Burn and Purify toxic waste using the same method as Syngas.

The last liquid material needed for the processing Uninspected Minerals!

You could set up another Lab Oven, or add Sodium Cyanide to the server of one of your other Lab Ovens. It will take some tinkering to get everything just right.

Highly recomended to use the recipe for Sodium Cyanide Plus, as it gives twice as much for the same amount of Liquid Ammonia.

Use this after every update to insure you have the latest version of the Questbook.

§l§lThis seems to cause a crash when used on a server, use the command §c§l/bq_admin default load §r§linstead!
Use a Gas Burner to create Water Vapor.

4x ore processing, as well as a main component in the processing of Uninspected Minerals.

The Leaching Vat will also need two gas tanks supplied with Water Vapor, a Power Station supplied with Fuel, and a Server.

Each process will consume 160mb of Hydrocloric Acid, and 240mb of Sodium Hydroxide.

The Retention Vat operates much the same as the Leaching Vat, with the main difference being you aren't able to chose the §a§eCatagory§f of shard.

This will be your main source of Rare Earth minerals.

Supply with the Leachate byproduct from the Leaching Vat, or you can melt Gangues down in a Slurry Pond.

Also will need a Power Station with fuel and Server.

Place the Test Tube and a Graduated Cylinder in the Glassware Holder, then the last two Cylinders in the Cabinets.
Keep the Reaction Stabilizer supplied with Ferrous Catalysts, so your shards don't desolve.

When Extracting dusts from a shard, you will always recover §a§220%§r of the available minerals, plus a precentage of the remaining, equal to the §2§r§aRecovery Efficiency %§r.§r This amount can be raised by increasing the Reaction Intensity, which will also increase the amount of acid required per operation.

§6Dissolution Chance§r and §eStabilization§r determine the chance the shard will be lost, if you don't have Ferrous Catalyst's installed. Its recommended to attach a Catalyst Regenerator to the Reaction Stabilizer so you dont have to worry about that.

§rExtracted dusts will need to be piped out of the Lab Balance to be usable.

You will also need a Power Station with RF and Fuel, and a Server.

Pipe metal dust into the top of the Element Cabinet, making sure it has a Graduated Cylinder.

Your Power Station will need to be supplied with Fuel. 

§6Check the Mineral Sizer quest for an overview on how Rockhounding machines work.§e

§eVanadium§r is used for §eVanasteel§r. (2x Mekanisim frames)


§e§7Scandium§r is used for §e§7ScAl§r. (2x Thermal frames and Applied Energistics)


§e§7§8Molybdenum§r is used for §e§7§8Nemonic§r. (2x Advanced Rocketry frames)


§c§d§cChrome§r is much more common --the first three are only attainable through the entire RH chain-- but much more widely used.
Makes it heat 3x as fast, but will need to be replaced over time.

You will also need a Power Station supplied with RF, a server, and three gas tanks.

Used for the top tier speed upgrades.
Also need a Power Station with RF, and a gas tank filled with Argon.
The Casing Upgrade makes heating and compressing go 10x faster, and the Insulation Upgrade makes less heat and pressure escape with each craft.
Swapping your Gold Cataylsts out with Osmium ones will double your output of Ammonia.
Swapping your Graphite Cataylsts out with these will halve your needed input for any recipe.
Needs Fuel and RF. Used as the second to last step for making YAG gems.
Use this along with the Sulfur Plus recipe to double your output.
Placing this inside any Power Station that requires fuel (Syngas/Lava) will convert RF into fuel, allowing you to eventually run your entire chemical plant off of RF.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Finding The Right Gangue For You!
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
To effectively produce the materials you want, you will need to search for what it is in JEI.

In this case we are going to be producing Osmium, so go ahead and search for that. Narrow your search by adding "shard".

You should result in a selection of shards that have various §lPercentages §fof metals. Choose one that has what you want. Higher percentages of metals require more Acid to extract.

Next search for the §eCatagory§f of the selected Shard, adding "gangue" to your search.

Check the §aComminution §flevel of the chosen Gangue, then set your Mineral Sizer to that and add Uninspected Minerals.
This and upgraded versions can be used in both machines that use gravity to select shards, and they narrow the range.

When choosing your Shard, remember there are two types, produced in the Leaching Vat, or the Renention Vat.

Once you have your Gangue, its time to extract the Shards. In the Leaching Controller, set the §dGravity §fto approximately what it shows for your chosen shard, then add your Gangue. If you have set everything up properly, you should end up with about 4 shards from that §dGravity §frange. 

You can complete this quest with either shard that contains Osmium.
Pipe Crude Oil inside as the first processing step.

Assemble a hollow 3x3x4 (you can click the show hologram button after you place your Blast Furnace to show you how to build it.)

By filling the center with lava, you can increase the heat to just over 1500, enough for Aluminum!

§bYou can place a Blast Furnace controller on each side of the structure.
Replacing the casing with Reinforced will increase heat by 20 each, for a total of 680.

Right click the Blast Furnace with 4 Kanthal Coils to increase heat by 500.

§bYou can make carbon plates by using a block of charcoal in a Metal Press.
Drop Stardust and a Rock Crystal into liquid starlight to grow.

The final upgrade, Advanced Machine Casings, each count for an additonal 20 heat.

Chrome is found by electrolizing Ruby dust.
Right clicking the Blast Furnace with 4 Nichrome Coils will increase heat by another 500.
Cast yourself a Reinforced level Pickaxe head. (Steel, Manasteel, Thaumium)
Each one gives 2 mins of flight.
Needed for the tier 4 Altar.

Collect a set of Wizard Robes.

Recharge with mana in the Arcane Workbench.

§l§l§l§rFlip to Heavy Machinery > Crusher in your Engineer's Manual, then craft it together with the Projector to configure it.§r

Middle Click with the Projector to rotate, then left click to anchor your hologram, then place the blocks as shown. Shift-right click on a block with the Projector to remove the Hologram if you want to move it.

After you finish, right click one of the center fences with the Engineer's Hammer to complete the machine!

Throw Coke Coal into the top to create some Coke Dust.

This can also be used to double ore, just feed it through the Crusher and you will get two dusts, along with a chance at a byproduct!

Craft a Sealing Sigil, then throw it into a 2x2 pool of water surrounded by flowers.

You can find Glowstone and Starmetal hanging on the inside of a Hollow Hill, along with lots of other ores, loot, and monsters.

§bMight be a good idea to bring some Data Models along with you!
Place this in the center of a 15x15 flat area, and insert a Attuned Trail Key.

Now that you can mine Obsidian, feel free to go to the Nether! 

If you already found your own way there, this quest will complete automatically.

A heavy arcane infused metal.

§bHint: Greatwood is a good source of Magic Essence.

Reuse the Projector from the last quest.

Hammer the center barrel to complete the Industral Squeezer.

You can also create plant oil here, which is one of the ingreidents for Bio-Desiel.

You can use the hammer on the piston to rotate it, then again once it is in the proper position to complete the Metal Press.

Use a Metal Press Mold on the Metal Press, then drop or pipe items on or into the back convayor block.
Cast yourself a Hardened level pickaxe head and go mining!

Right click with a redstone torch to toggle pulse mode, which will only fire the laser then it gets a redstone signal. 

Dropping or placing things in the laser will convert them into various things, try it out!

§bFor now you can power it with Embers.
Place this in the upgrade slot for 2x Speed.
These store one type of item, in very high quantitys.

When the Drawer Controller is placed adjacent to any amount of connected drawers within a certain distance, it will serve as the access point for all of them.

Slaves count as Controllers for input and output, but cannot be used on their own.
Placing an item with a block and/or nugget form inside of a Compacting Drawer will allow each variety to be accesable.
Placing down the Framing Table, then adding the Framed Drawer as well as a block or two, will allow for custom made drawers.

Use these on a placed drawer to customize its storage capabilities. Shift-right clicking on a drawer with an empty hand will open its interface, allowing you to remove or modify the upgrades currently in use.

Use the Key on a drawer with an item in it, and it will stay that item even if you have 0 inside. Locking an empty drawer will change it to only accept manual input until used. 

Check out the other keys and upgrades for more useful things.
3x Speed.
4x Speed.
5x Speed.
6x Speed.
7x Speed.
8x Speed.

The left side is where you place your ores to be smelted, or your alloy bases. The right side is where you put your additives. Your Graphite Electrodes are placed in the top.

Slag can be piped out the back, and your final product out the front.
Look for the giant hedge maze, and slay the great Naga!
Craft up a batch of Refined Iron!
Now that you have 2500+ heat, you can smelt your Osmium into ingots.
Pour some lava into the workbench, then place the correct tool inside.

Pipe a Rockhounding gas into this, then activate the proper module. If done correctly, you should see the output and input tanks filling up. Now simply pipe it out as a liquid.

This can also be done in reverse.

§d§5§fRight click to link the Blood Orb to you. It is used in crafting, and placing it in a filled altar will store LP (Blood) for rituials and the Alchemy Table.

A basic block for building some multiblock machines.

Place a Ember Shard along with 4 ingots worth of the correct molten metal into the stamp base. Be sure that you have the Shard placed first, otherwise you will end up with 4 plates.

Next place a bucket of Starlight down, and drop the Aspectus' inside to activate them.

§bHint: By placing a non infused Aspectus inside of a Light Well, you can collect molten metal of that type. This will average to about 6 ingots (at night) worth per Aspectus.

You will need Clear glass to make these, which is just melted sand cast in a basin in the melter.

This is the first Ender IO Conduit you'll be using. Right click on the base of a connection, or shift left click with a wrench to edit it. Up to 4 different types of Conduits can be in the same space.

If you click on the gear icon in the tank's GUI you can set each side to push or pull fluids without needing a pipe.

This will be enough resources to construct a 3x3x1 inside Smeltery. Place 9 blocks in a square for the base, then one row up place the rest on each side so there is a 3x3 area surounded by bricks. 

Fuel goes in the tank, and ore in the controller. The Drain functions similarly to how the Melter did; simply attach a Faucet to one of the sides and right click or supply with redstone to pour molten metal into a Casting table or Basin.

The Smeltery can create alloys out of various types of metals, so be careful what you put in!

With this you can create custom armor.

Purple slime can be found on floating islands, though you will need to be creative with your ascent. (Hint: try building with sand)
With this you can create much more advanced tools and weapons.

Turn in 64 Iron to complete the first chapter.

Because making a Tinkers tool is not technically required, this quest is to allow you to make it to this point without following the book.
Grinding Will by killing mobs is old school. Cycle through the rituals until you get to the §4Gathering of the Forsaken Souls.
No Description
Quests coming Soon (TM)
This can be used to summon a §1§r§b§r§9Spirit§r to make Specter Ingots later.
Used to make Singularities and Matter Balls.

For use in the RF Tools Builder.

§6Requires a Nuclear Reactor to create.
Pipe your Coal Tar byproduct from creating Syngas into a Heavy Drum, then pipe the liquid Coal Tar into a Lab Oven along with Water and Cracked Lime.
Assemble a Lab Oven and run the Ammonia by Tar recipe.
Installing a Gas Turbine in any Power Station requiring RF will allow it to use fuel instead.
Once your network gets big enough, you will need some Energy Cells to help it stay online.
Place the crank on top, and hold right click on it to use.
Used to make Bound Weapons and Blood Iron.
Fluid storage.
Upgrade by using Kits on these.
No Description
Unlocks the Nuclear Engineering Chapter!
Look up the molten recipes to create.
The End. Kinda.
Congratulations! You made it this far! I'm super proud of you.
Depending on which Vis Crystals you use, you can give Arcane Stone the ability to block mobs or increase your movement speed.

Used for the Laser Core of the Void Miner.

Can also be melted down into Molten Neodymium Doped YAG, which can be used to make §dNeodymium Doped YAG Rods§f.

Place the Paper in your research station, then start your research. Selecting an icon will give some direction for what options show up.

Placing related blocks around your station might give you more starting options. The bookshelf is the guide for Fundamentals.

Remember, be sure to unlock everything through the Thaumonomicon.
Can be used to process ore for byproducts.
Crushes things.
Used in the production of Aluminum, among other things.
The recipe for Block of Biotite requires you to have at least 2 Transformer upgrades in the Compressor.
Craft Heating Coils and easy Sheetmetal with this.
Great way to process Rubber.
Might want to look into starting a Bonsai farm for rubber.

Can make some recipes cheaper.

This machine is suuuuuuuuuuuuper slow, so here is a few overclockers for now.
Having these on your head or in a bauble slot will allow you to see aspects inside the Crucible.
Dropping things into Mana is a good idea.
Use this like a Casting Table until you can craft the Basin Upgrade.
Getting into Agricraft about now eh? By creating a line of double sticks, with a seed planted at one end, will allow you to improve the stats as it spreads.
You can use a tank with oil in place of the bucket for Treated Planks.

You will need a steel ingot to build this, but it is a faster alternative to the Windmill.

Up to 3 Water Wheels can be attached together on a single Dynamo.

By hammering each side of the Capacitor with the Engineers Hammer, you can switch betwean input and output for that side. 

After you have placed a Wire Connector on your power input, and another one on the machine you want to be powered, right click both with a Wire.

You can also connect multiple wires to one Wire Relay.

Right click each blade of the Windmill with a Sail to increase the speed.

These can be crafted one at a time.
Turn fruit or sugarcane into Ethanol.
Combine Ethanol and Plant Oil into Biodiesel.
Supply with fuel, start with Biodiesel. Outputs 4096 RF a tick.
This machine requires over 4k power to run, but will never run out of ores.

Place the Beam Cannon facing the Exchange Tablet, with the Pedestals nearby.

The relevant Aspectus go in the Pedestals, then place the minimum amount of ash in each one.

Power the Beam Cannon with Embers, then supply a redstone signal to fire at the Exchange Table.

The recipe will fail, and you'll be left with some waste that will inform you of the exact amount of ash needed to correctly perform the recipe.

The Funnel and Injector act the same as their smaller counterparts.

The Splitter accepts Embers on the small side, with the big sides actting as Emmiters.


Place a Machanical Core or Machine Accessor underneath the Crystal Cell to allow access. The Accessor wont connect if shift-right clicked onto the bottom.

Piping Ember Crystals in will increase the Ember storage.
Pretty handy for automation.
One of the best Alloy Smelters in the game.
Smelt things with RF. What more can you ask for. Wait, two things?!
Power transfer and storage up to 1024 RF/tick.
Useful for caving.

Shift-Right click a corner, then right click the opposite corner to copy a structure. 

After you have it set up how you want, hold G to swap to Paste mode.


You can also place it along with a piece of paper into the Template Manager to save your pattern for later usage.
Use Fuel to boil water for your Steam Turbine.

This Multiblock will require you to make the Arc Furnace first, for Aluminum and Electrical Steel.

Use these two multiblocks to turn steam into high amounts of energy, up to 4096 RF/tick each connection.

§cThis path requires you to get to the Arc Furnace before actually making any power.

§rAn alternate method of generating power through steam. This method is more expensive, but will save you automation.
One of the main metals to create your AE Network.

To craft anything with this table, you need enough starlight, then to hit the table with the Resonating Wand.

§6Claiming this quest will unlock the required research for crafting!

The Resonating Wand is used to start Starlight crafting by using it on the table after the icon of the craft shows up.

The Morphing Tool is used similar to the Akashic Tome, but it will automagicly switch to the correct tool.

Holding the Resonating Wand at night will highlight nearby underground Rock Crystal Ore.

Each Rock Crystal Ore can drop more then one Rock Crystal, each of which has unique properties. By holding shift when hovering over a crystal, you can see its properties.

Aquamarine, Rock Crystals, and Celestial Crystals will create liquid starlight over time when placed in the Lightwell, eventually being destroyed.

Lightwells only hold 2 buckets at a time, and are only able to pipe fluids out the bottom. They are also about 3 times more effective at night.

Using an Aspectus will create approximately twice the amount of molten metal required to create them.

Assembling one of these structures, as shown in your Astral Tome, by your Altar will increase the amount of avalible Starlight. Not as needed at first, but as you progress there will be some crafts that will require more.
Illumanation Powder is used to light up an area, and Nocturnal Powder can summmon aggressive mobs to fight.

Using the §bLooking Glass§r during the night will allow you to see Constellations you have discovered. By tracing then as shown by your Constellation Pages, you can memorize them!

The §6Sextant§r will also show a hologram of the required structure when used on a upgraded Starlight Crafting Table.

Holding the §1§9Fosic Resonator§r at night will show you areas of concentrated Starlight. Placing your Astral crafting station there will increase the total amount of starlight avalible to use.
Place the Rope and Nails 4 blocks apart, then right click them with the Hammock.
Dropping a variety of foods will create mana.
Hot on one side, cold on the other.
Only way to make gold wires.
Freezer goes on top of 3x3 casings.
Tilling grass has a chance to drop Worms, which can be used to keep a 3x3 area of ground watered and fertilized.

You can make carbon plates by using a block of charcoal in a Metal Press.

§bCommon loot from Nether Fortresses!

This is the core craft for Tech Reborn, so batch crafting these would be in your favor. Also, look into the automated workbench!

Use Transformer upgrades to increase the max power input for machines.

Placing a Blueprint inside will allow you to select one of the designs for autocrafting.

Highly recommended to create a few of these to automate circuits.

Place a Blueprint in to access unique or cheaper recipes.

Also used to apply shaders and modify tools and weapons from Immersive Engineering.

§bCraft the Drill together with the filled Jerrycan to fill it. You can refill the can by placing it into your Refinery full of Biodeisel once you get that far.
Starting your storage network! Connect a chest with the §dStorage Link Cable§r or a §bSimple Cable§r to access it through your Storage Request Table.

Use the power of the sun to create steam.

Assemble the Solar Tower as shown, with up to four Solar Reflectors around it.

Can set an input and output with the Processing Cable, and access all Processing Cables in the Controller.

For example, if you connect a Cable to a furnace, and set one piece of wood as the input and one piece of Charcoal as the output, you could request Charcoal in your Controller and it would do it for you.
The first wireless terminal. Check what you can make with this for the next tier remote.

By placing a Rock Crystal on this and turning it, you will trade some Size for Cutting.

Dropping a Rock Crystal into placed Liquid Starlight, it will absorb it over time to increase its Size.

Once it reaches the max Size, it will split into two, which have the chance to be higher Purity.

This setup is much more expensive, but will save on channels.

The multiblock is made by placing Frames on the edges of a 4x4x4 cube, then the Vents on the 6 empty sides, along with the Controller and I/O Port. Fill the inside with the Crafting Coprocessors and Pattern Providers. When finished, right click on the Controller to activate the multiblock.


You can make this as big as you want, with any combination of Coprocessors and Pattern Providers.
Who's got time to look all over finding fallen rocks?
Even more ores!
There should be a better way...
This is used to transform blocks by linking a Collector Crystal to them. They are found in the large astral temples, and will need a view on the sky to function.
Rock Crystals placed on the pedestal cause various effects depending on the attunment.
Acts similar to the Looking Glass, but can be placed and snaps to the constellations.
Place will into the forge to start a craft.

Allows travel between any Gateways. You could make a star gate network for every dimension you need to travel to.

Name the Gateway in the anvil before placing it to see where you are going.
Place a filled Blood Orb to craft. Some crafts require higher tiers of orbs.

By holding a Consellation Paper in your off hand you will see where to place the Relays on the field. If the matching Constellation is in the sky, it will light up and you will be able to attune yourself or Rock Crystals by being on top of the Attunement Altar.

§bYou can get to level 100 in this pack, so go crazy!

Place the §eAlembic§r on top with the §6Filling Transfuser§r attached to it, and after placing some jars nearby you'll start to see Essentia filling them!

This version is 90% efficient, with the rest turned into §dFlux§r. The waste can be lowered by attaching one or more §9Auxiliary Venting Ports§r to the sides.

Attaching a §9Auxiliary Slurry Pump§r to the side, with another §eAlembic§r on top, will allow it to process Aspects twice as fast.
This advanced crafting altar is used for many things. Check in the Tome or use the Sextant to see how to assemble the structure.

Use the Core Sample Drill in various chunks to find a good location to build your Pumpjack. 

After placing the drill and supplying power, right click it to start. Right click it again to extract the sample. Use your Engineers Manual to see what each ore vein will give if you build an Excavator on it.

Each chunk has a different type of vein, and you can turn on chunk borders by pressing F9.

Shift right click to place the Samples.
Use the Sextant on the altar after upgrading to show a hologram of the required temple.

Drop items on top, then fill with Mana. Once full, drop a Livingrock and right click with your Wand of the Forest.

§bHint: if you place a spreader next to a filled pool, and point it at the altar, it will start to fill up the altar as soon as it needs mana.
Assemble the arena as shown in the Lexica Botania.

Place the Empowerer, with the Display Stands three blocks away on each side.

Each Display Stand needs power to craft.

Place a Spark over the Plate, and the other over a Mana Pool at least half full. Then drop or right click the correct items on and watch the light show!

More then one linked Mana Pool will allow you to perform the craft faster.

Place the Pylons over two Mana Pools at least half full each. Use the Lexa Botania to display the hologram to assemble the portal, then right click on the core to activate!

Throw items in to exchange for the Elven equivalant.
Accend the Lich's tower and battle the Lich.
An early game power option.
Explore the deadly Labyrinth in search of the Minoshroom.
Travel to a Fire Swamp and slay the Hydra!
Be sure to bring a trophy!
Climb the tricky tower and slay all those who oppose you.
Look out for Judy!
Otherwise known as the Ice Queen.

§bRight click with the Resonating Wand to start the craft, or use 2 Automated Users, one to place the item and one to start the craft with the wand.
Welcome to Mekanism!
Welcome to Thermal!

No Description

§bCrafted with +1 Amber and 1 Salis Mundus per level in the Infusion Matrix, along with Vitreus, Praemunio, and Potentia essence.

Yikes, thats a lot of essence.
Any Empowered item can be done in block form. Either item will complete the quest.
Drop into a mana pool, requires some mana to be in it already.
This combination will make you the talk of the town!
The highest tier.
Use up some of that HDPE!
Kill a Specter with something that deals magic damage, such as a Wizardry or Thaumcraft spell.
Unlimited uses!
An advanced alloy smelter, can also be used to process ores

Important metals.
Crafted in a normal crarfting table.
Processing Bauxite is one of the main ways to get Titanium. Can't quite smelt it yet though.
Configure your Blood Magic book to show you the tier three layout, then place the §620 runes §rand Voidstone as shown. The Pillars can be made of any material.
Wear this along with some portable mana for speed and auto step.
These make it slightly less urgent to explore.
Right click on a normal chest to upgrade.
Even bigger then an Iron Chest!

§9Quantum Minecraft Dynamics §fis a mod that brings §5High-Energy Particle Physics§f to Minecraft. While it may seem complicated at first glance, the mod becomes much more understandable when you understand the concepts behind it. 

Besides this in-game quest book guide, §9Quantum Minecraft Dynamics § also h§has its own §2Guide Book§r already present in the Akashic Tome (albeit incomplete). A more complete version can be found on the §Q§Q§2QMD Github Wiki.§f

Of course, the §N§2Nuclearcraft Official Discord§r also has channels to discuss high-energy particle smashing! Make sure to check out §7#qmd§r for support.

Without further ado, let's get into the tutorial!

In short, the entire mod revolves around manipulating §5particles§f to do various things. §5Particles§f are created and accelerated in §3§1§9§b§3Linear Accelerators§f, accelerated further in §3Synchrotron Accelerators§f, then used for recipes in various §3multiblock machines§f, including:

§3§f- Target Chamber
- Collision Chamber
- Neutral Exotic Containment
- Decay Chamber

These recipes produce new §eitems§f or even new types of §5particles§f, which can then be used in further recipes. All §3Multiblocks§f above will be gone into detail in subsequent quests. Since the entire mod revolves around §5particles§f, it is only natural that we understand how they work before we do anything involving them.

Much like how regular §eitems§f are stored in stacks, §5particles§f in §9QMD §fare stored in §""particle stacks"§f. However, unlike item stacks, particle stacks cannot be held by the player. Instead, §pparticle stacks§f can only be manipulated in §9QMD's §3Multiblock Machines§f, many of which were mentioned above, and transported between said machines via§7 §8beamline pipes.§f Even within said §3Multiblocks§f, particles are transported via §7§8beam blocks§f.

Particle stacks have 3 properties:
§4- Amount (pu/t)
§6- Energy (eV)
§b- Focus§f

All recipes require particle stacks to have a minimum §bfocus§f and to be within a certain §6energy range (e.g 10-20 MeV)§f for the recipe to work (relevant values can be seen in §2JEI§f). §3
§A§fAs most newly-created particles start out with no §6energy §fand barely any §bfocus§f, §3Accelerators§e §fare used in order to get particle stacks to the relevant § §6energy§f and §bfocus§f§f. How §3Accelerators§f do this, and how they are constructed will be covered in the next quest. 

Besides being used as a requirement in some recipes, §bfocus §falso determines how far a given particle stack will travel. This is because a particle stack loses a certain amount of §bfocus§f per §8beamline pipe/beam block§f travelled (the amount of §bfocus§f lost per block is the attenuation rate of the relevant block, seen in their tooltip). A particle stack with a §a§bfocus§f less than or equal to zero will not travel any further. 

§fThe §4amount§f of §d§5particles§e§f in the particle stack determines the rate of §eitem §fproduction and §4amount§f of new §5particles §e§fproduced from said recipe (can be seen and calculated from §2JEI§f information). Unlike §6energy §for §bfocus§f, §3Accelerators§f cannot directly affect a particle stack's §4amount (pu/t)§f. A particle stack's §4amount§f is solely dependent on the source of the §5particle§f, as will be seen in the next quest and subsequent quests.

This is where the §5particle§f beam from your §3Linear Accelerator§f, and subsequently any setup, will be input into the §aTarget Chamber§f. 

If the recipe outputs §d§5particles§f you would like to use in other recipes, simply extend 1-3 more §7Beam Block§f lines from 1-3 of the remaining sides of the §7Particle Chamber Block§f to the casing, and place §8§7Particle Chamber Beam Ports§f in output mode where they meet the casing. Neutral §5particles§f will come out of the side opposite of the input, while charged §5particles§f will come out of the remaining two sides (the direction can be changed by shift right clicking the relevant §7Particle Chamber Beam Port§f with the multitool). A screenshot of a §aTarget Chamber§f can be found on the §2QMD§f §2Github Wiki§f.

§cThe particle chamber must be connected directly to the linear accelerator via a beamline pipe, otherwise particles will not be transported from the linear accelerator to the particle chamber!

§fIf your §aTarget Chamber§f has been supplied with §eitems§f and §5particles§f within the recipe's §6energy range§f exceeding the recipe's required §bfocus§f, as well as power, the §aTarget Chamber§f will start processing the recipe, producing new §eitems§f and §5particles§f (if any) which are output as particle stacks from the output §7Particle Chamber Beam Ports.

§fThe time taken for a recipe to process, in ticks, is given as the §4amount§f of §5particles§f required for the recipe (e.g 120kpu) divided by the §4amount§f of §5particles§f in the particle stack (e.g 100 pu/t). In this case, the recipe will take 60s to process.

The resulting §5particle§f§5s§e §fand their particle stack properties can be seen in the target chamber§f GUI. More details on how the resulting particle stack properties are calculated can be found in the "Target Chamber Maths" quest.

You've finally done it: the laws of physics §c§rbend§r* before your engineering might, as you hit rocks together so hard they make §6§rgold§r. Now, you need to put those skills to the test: §d§eP-Type Doped Silicon §fis your aim. 

If you've followed the tutorial, you should now have a §3Linear Accelerator§f capable of accelerating§5 Boron Ions§f to between §6600KeV and 1MeV§f, as well as a §bfocus§f greater than §b2§f. This §3Linear Accelerator§f should be directly connected via §8Beamline Pipes§f to a §aTarget Chamber§f containing §eSilicon Wafers§f.

Before switching on your §3Linear Accelerator§f, first:

1. Make sure both your §3Linear Accelerator §fand §aTarget Chamber§f are powered with sufficient power.

2. Make sure that the total §9cooling§f exceeds the total §cheating§f in your §3Linear Accelerator§f.

3. Make sure that your §3Linear Accelerator§f has been topped up with the appropiate §1coolant§f and has been cooled below the maximum temperature as shown in the §3Accelerator§f GUI, and that the supercooler cooling loop has been set up.

Now, simply place §eDiborane Canisters§f in the Ion Source§f and give the Linear Accelerator Controller§f a §4redstone signal§f, and the §aTarget Chamber§f should produce §eP-Type Doped Silicon§f.

Congratulations! You've built your first complete §9QMD§f setup and manufactured your first §9QMD§f item!

Due to the vast differences in §5particles §fand §5particle properties§f§f required in different recipes, you'll probably have to construct an entirely new setup for each new §eitem§f you make. However, the basic principles remain the same: accelerate §5particles§f until their §6energy§f and §bfocus§f match that required by the recipe. 

All the best on your §9QMD§f journey!

*Disclaimer: The laws of physics don't actually bend before your engineering might, as you're using the laws of physics to their fullest extent to accelerate §5particles§f to immense speeds. Apologies in advance for ruining your moment of victory.

Blasting metals in the §aTarget Chamber§f with §5particles§f at even higher §6energies§f, in the §61GeV-20GeV§f range, produces §eSpallation Waste§f. These piles of metal have undergone fusion, allowing you to turn basic metals such as §eLead§r into much more interesting metals like§§ §eIridium§r or §eHafnium§r!

These collisions also produce §5exotic new particles§f, which will be very useful for producing exotic fluids like §6antimatter§f or §6muonium§f later.

Your reactor just keeps making all this §7High-Pressure Steam§r! If only there was some convenient multiblock structure you could use to process that into §eslightly ludicrous amounts of power§r!

Enter the §9Turbine§r: steam goes in, power comes out the coils. It's all quite simple; however, be warned: if you put §c§rmore steam in§r than the turbine can handle, it will spin too fast and §cexplode§r! Avoid this by using the §aReactor Planner§r to make sure it can handle §7more mB/t§r than your reactors produce. Did I mention you can make §9one big turbine§r and run the outputs of all of your reactors into it?

Particle physics isn't §oall§r big, dangerous structures for making things go fast and then explode; it's also big, dangerous §cguns§r for making things go fast and then explode!

The §eLepton Cannon§r is an extremely advanced particle weapon that uses various leptons such as §6Tauonium§r as ammunition to annihilate those pesky mobs trying to steal your trade secrets! Refinement of this §6material§r will require some pretty advanced §3multiblocks§f; check §2JEI§f to see what steps of particle collision you need to create the §5Tau§o§r and §5Anti-Tau§r particles, before putting them into a §7Neutral Containment Unit§r for storage in cells!

§cTauonium requires the highest collision energy in the mod; you will need to accelerate protons to 150GeV to make Tauonium via Higgs decay. Good luck.§f

Give em' hell, Gordon.

Contrary to the title of this quest, the §eGluon Gun§r is not actually a weapon! This handheld cannon is an extremely powerful §cmining tool§r, capable of digging massive tunnels in seconds. Of course, this comes at a cost: it runs off of §5Glueballs§r! Don't let the ordinary name fool you; you will need §7numerous particle collision steps§r in order to make this type of matter.

§cGlueballs require the second highest collision energy in the mod; you will need to accelerate protons and antiprotons to 100GeV to make glueballs. Good luck.

The §aCollision Chamber§r allows you to take two particle beams and §csmash them together§r! This has two primary functions. The first is to construct §5larger matter/antimatter particles§f from more basic particles like §5protons, antiprotons and deuterons.§f This requires particle beams with very low, but not zero, §6energy§f to converge in the §aCollision Chamber§f. The second is to smash two §6extremely high energy§f particle beams to produce §5new, exotic particles§f! Both come with their own challenges, as will be detailed later.

To construct a §aCollision Chamber, §fconstruct a 17 long cuboid of §7Particle Chamber Casings or Glass.§f The ends must be squares of odd size from 3 to 15 across, however there is no point in constructing one larger than 11x11. There must also be a §7Collision Chamber Controller§f and a §7Particle Chamber Energy Port§f in the casing. Down the middle of the long axis, there must be a line of §7Particle Chamber blocks.§f 

At each end, there must be a §7Particle Chamber Beam Port in input mode.§f 2 blocks away from each square end, on the horizontals, there must be§7 Particle Chamber Beam Blocks§f connecting the Particle Chamber axis to §7Particle Chamber Beam Ports in output mode.§f  The two input §5particles§f are inserted through the opposite input §7Beam Ports§f, while output §5particles§f are outputted through the four output §7Beam Ports§f. The port which they are output from can be changed by shift right clicking the §7Beam Port§f with a multitool - this switches the output slot of the §7Beam Port§f with the one clockwise of it, viewed from the top. A screenshot of a §aCollision Chamber§f can be found on the §2QMD Github Wiki.§f 

In order for a recipe to work, both input particle beams must have a §bfocus§f above 5 and §6energy§f above that shown in §2JEI§f. The sum of the input particle beam's §6energies§f must be within the §6energy range§f stated in §2JEI§f. If these requirements are met and the §aCollision Chamber§f is powered, it will start processing the recipe, producing new §5particles§f as particle stacks which are output through the four output §7Beam Ports§f. 

The resulting §5particle§f§5s§e §fand their particle stack properties can be seen in the collision chamber GUI. More details on how the resulting particle stack properties are calculated can be found on the §2QMD Github Wiki.§f

Much like other §aParticle Chambers§f, §aCollision Chambers§f can also have detectors placed in them, increasing their efficiency. A higher efficiency increases the §4amount§f of §5particles§f in the resulting particle stacks, although the §4amount§f may never be higher than that stated in §2JEI§f. Detectors are primarily useful for §aCollision Chamber§f recipes with very low cross-sections, especially the §6high-energy§f collisions. More details on the §4amount§f calculation for output particle stacks and efficiency can be found on the §2QMD Github Wiki§f.

The remaining portion of this quest will cover common challenges in completing §aCollision Chamber§f recipes.

The main challenge in the first function of the §aCollision Chamber§f, which is combining beams of §5particles§f at very low non-zero §6energies§f, is decelerating the §5particles§f to a very low §6non-zero energy§f. Even with §3Decelerator §4redstone control§f, the lowest §6non-zero energy§f (i.e. 1/15th of the maximum §6particle beam energy§f the §3Decelerator§f may decelerate as determined by the formula E=Ef(1-Sr/15)) may already exceed the limit set in §2JEI§f (typically 10MeV). 

One way to circumvent this is to ensure that the energy of the §5particle§f producing the §5antiparticle§f in the §aTarget Chamber§f is as close to the §6minimum energy§f as possible. This ensures that the §5antiparticles§f produced are of §6low energy§f, thus a weak §3Decelerator§f whose lowest §6non-zero energy§f is below the limit set in §2JEI§f may be used.

Another way to solve this problem is to use a §3Linear Accelerator§f to accelerate a particle beam which has had its §6energy§f reduced to 0eV by a §3Decelerator§f. §3Linear Accelerators§f are still able to accelerate 0eV particle beams, and offer much finer control over the §6energy§f of an output §5particle§f than §3Synchrotrons§f or §3Decelerators§f, making them perfect for accelerating particle beams to the §6low non-zero energies§f required in such recipes.

The main challenge in the second function of the §aCollision Chamber§f, which is to smash two §6extremely high energy§f particle beams together, is building a §3Synchrotron§f capable of accelerating §5particles§f to those §6high energies§f. §aCollision Chambers§f demand §6extremely high energies§f in the range of §6100GeV-150GeV§f. As it is a lot easier to accelerate §5heavy particles§f rather than §5light particles§f, due to them being affected by different factors, it is recommended that you pick the recipes involving §5protons§f or §5antiprotons§f, and avoid the recipe involving §5electrons§f and §5positrons§f. Even then, it's highly recommended that you read up on the formulas governing the output§6 energy§f of an output beam from a §3Synchrotron§f, and use those to calculate a §3Synchrotron§f powerful enough for these recipes.

Good luck completing the §aCollision Chamber§f recipes!

The §7Neutral Containment Chamber§r creates §6neutrally charged exotic matter§f from one or more particle beams, and stores such §6matter§f safely in itself. These fluids can also be transferred to special §econtainment cells§f. These filled §econtainment cells§f can then be used in various gadgets and recipes.

To construct a §7Neutral Containment Chamber§r§f, construct a 7x7x7 or 9x9x9 cube of §7Containment Casing or Glass.§f In the centre of each side face, a §7Containment Beam Port or Containment Laser§f must be placed, and 2 of each must be placed opposite of each other in a §7Containment Chamber§f. There must be a §7Containment Coolant Vent§f in input and output modes as well as a §7Containment Energy Port§f. Inside, on the top and bottom, there must be a ring of §7Containment Coils§f with the sides of the ring one block away from the walls of the Chamber. A screenshot of a §7Neutral Containment Chamber§r§f§f can be found on the §2QMD Github Wiki§f.

The §7Neutral Containment Chamber§f must be constantly supplied with power and §1active coolant§f that is capable of §9cooling§f it below the maximum operating temperature, much like an §3Accelerator§f. 

Make sure the needs of the§7 Neutral Containment Chamber§f are constantly met! If any of the below happen while it contains §6exotic fluid§f:

- Runs out of power
- Temperature rises above the maximum operating temperature
- The Chamber is broken

The Chamber will fail, leading to §4catastrophic§f results!

In order to create §6exotic matter§f, the required particle beams as stated in §2JEI§f must have an §6energy§f of §60eV§f (with the exception of §5glueballs§f, which can have any §6energy§f) and a §bfocus§f greater than that listed in §2JEI§f. If the particle beams required meet the criteria, §6exotic matter§f is created. The number of ticks it takes to create 1mb of §6exotic matter§f is the §4amount§f of §5particles§f required for the recipe, divided by the §4amount§f of §5particles§f in the particle stack. If there are two beams, the time taken will be the larger of the two beams.

To fill a §ecell§f with §6exotic matter§f, simply pipe an empty §ecell§f into the chamber via the controller or a §7Containment Item Port§f, and the chamber will automatically fill the cell with the §6exotic matter§f it is currently holding.

§eBSCCO §fis an advanced §6high-temperature superconductor alloy§f. It's used in wire form to create numerous incredibly advanced machines; its most notable use, of course, is in §eElite Processors§r.

§eStrontium§f is an important material only obtainable via §9QMD§f. It's required to manufacture §eBSCCO§f, a superconductor material required for further progression in the mod.

There are two main ways of making §eStrontium§f. The first way is obtaining §eStrontium§f from §eLight Fission Waste§f. While this method is feasible for obtaining trace amounts of §eStrontium§f, it is slow and takes a long time to obtain mass amounts of §eStrontium§f.

The second, much faster way is striking §eZirconium§r with §5Neutrons§f in a §aTarget Chamber§f. While this method is more challenging than the first method, as a §5neutron§f of the right §6energy§f must be procured from a seperate §aTarget Chamber§f recipe, this method is much more feasible for obtaining §eStrontium§f, especially if you're planning to use §eElite Processors §fto make §eEV Capacitors§f.

Hint: One of the §eitems§f you need to manufacture for later use produces §5neutrons§f as a byproduct. If only you could find a way to make it produce a §5neutron§f of the correct §6energy§f...

§6Muonium§f is made from combining §5Muons§f and §5Anti-Muons§f in a §7Neutral Containment Chamber§f. The simplest way to make §6muonium§f has already been detailed in a questline, but if you're feeling daring, you can attempt to make §6muonium§f from the other methods involving §aCollision Chamber§f recipes as well. 

You'll need quite a fair bit of this to make §eNeutronic Matrixes§f for §8Neutronium, §fso make sure to fully automate it!

§6Anti-Helium 3§f is made by combining §5Anti-Helion§f and §5Positrons §fin a §7Neutral Containment Chamber§f. 

While there are several methods of obtaining §5Positrons§f, the simplest is using a §eSodium-22 Source§f in a §3Linear Accelerator§f. §3Linear Accelerators§f can accelerate §5particles§f at §60eV§f, thus you only need to raise the §bfocus§f of the §5positron§f to be greater than §b2§f.

§5Anti-Helion§f is obtained via collision of §5Anti-Protons and Anti-Deuterons§f in a §aCollision Chamber§f. The tricky part is the §6energy§f - the recipe requires both particle beams to have an §6energy above 700MeV§f and for their §6combined energy§f to be less than §610MeV§f. However, there are a few ways of solving this problem, which are detailed in the "Small Hadron Collider" quest. It's up to you how you want to obtain §5anti-protons and anti-deuterons§f - §2JEI§f showcases multiple ways of making both.

As you only need one §eincoherent matrix§f to get all the §5Filons§f you need, you won't need much §6Anti-Helium 3§f, but constructing the entire setup will still be a challenge!
The §eIncoherent Matrix§f is used to produce §5Filons§f in an §8Ion Source§f. As it has no durability, you'll only need one of these to produce as many §5Filons§f as you need.

The §eNeutronic Matrix§f is used as the base material in a §aTarget Chamber§f which the §5Filon§f collides with to produce §9§8Neutronium§f. You'll need one of these for each §8Neutronium Ingot§f you want to produce.

This quest chain will be a useful walkthrough of one method of obtaining §6Muonium§r. Hopefully, it will get you acquainted with the methods used when turning particles into other particles to produce a particular end product.

To start the process, you need to strike a §emetal§f in a §aTarget Chamber§f to produce §eSpallation Waste§r at a high enough §6energy§f to produce §5Pions§r. This will produce both §cpositive§r and §9negative§r pions; we will need both for our §9§rend product§r.

The §aDecay Chamber§r allows you to decompose the §5particles§f in a beam into their §5constituent particles§r. This can be very important for turning huge particles like §5Alpha Particles§r into smaller components for refining.

§aDecay Chambers§f are constructed exactly like §aTarget Chambers§f, only with a §7Decay Chamber Controller§f instead. A screenshot of a §aDecay Chamber§r can be found on the §2QMD Github Wiki.§f 

The §aDecay Chamber§f also requires power and a §5particle beam§f. The resulting §5particles§f and their particle stack properties can be seen in the decay chamber GUI, and are calculated the same way as §aTarget Chambers§f as detailed in the "Target Chamber Maths" quest.

§aDecay Chambers§f can also have detectors installed in them to increase efficiency. Although efficiency won't increase the speed of the recipe in §aDecay Chambers§f, it will increase the §4amount§f of §5particles§f in the resulting particle stacks, although the §4amount§f may never be higher than that stated in §2JEI§f. More details on the §4amount§f calculation for output particle stacks can be found in the "Target Chamber Maths" quest.

These §5Pions§r are not too useful right now; we want to run both the §cpositive§r and §9negative§r streams through §aDecay Chambers§r in order to get the byproducts that we really need: §5Muons§r and §5Anti-Muons§r.

Now that you have both §5Muon§r and §5Anti-Muon§r particle beams, you will want to decelerate them to <1keV in a §3Decelerator§f, then converge both beams in a §7Neutral Containment Chamber§f. With enough power, these beams will condense into §6Muonium§r!
These are an important late-game material for multiblocks!

The §7Low-Gravity Deposition Chamber§f is used to deposit §6exotic matter§f onto specially-prepared §eDeposition Matrices§r. Due to its incredibly sensitive nature, it can §9only be built in space§r. This includes the moon or space stations.

Filling one of these with Starlight and placing it near the Starlight Infuser will automagically fill any places it was consumed during a craft.

You can also create Sky Stone by placing a second one filled with Tectonic Petrotheum near by!
Use these when you have a Dire need to make a lot happen in a little bit of time!

Tranquility Guide by §bDiamondSentinel§r:

-From here on, in each cardinal direction add another few rows of a type of path. 
-Wooden (3 rows past altar) caps at 60%, Stone (2 rows past wooden) caps at 120%, worn stone (2 rows past stone) caps at 200%, and obsidian (2 rows past worn stone) caps at 300%. 
-There are 7 categories of "tranquility" that you can gain. These blocks go on the same y coordinate as the paths, and up to 2 levels higher (so 3+ block tall trees don't help). Mix and match categories as much as you can, but don't bother with anything other than the best of each category. 
  §a §e-Crop - Potatoes, Carrots, Wheat, and Wart all give the same bonus. Pick your favorite. 
   §7-Earthen - Farmlands your best. Fortunate. 
   §c-Fire - Actual fire works best here. Light it on Netherack. (also gives a bonus)

Filling the Midnight Frames with Luminessence will make all crafts faster. With all 8 replaced its about a 60% speed buff.
Place an §dUnpackager§r with the other one of the pattern set next to one of these to process that recipe type.

§9§rThis quest will teach you the intricacies of how to keep §9Heat Sinks§r activated, §7Conductors§r, and about §bActive Moderator Blocks§r.

§9Heat Sinks §rcome in many different varieties, and each one has its own set of rules to be valid. 


Now the rules required to ensure active §9Heat Sinks. §r

1. They must start connected to a§6 Fuel Cell§r to be considered active. You'll want to make sure each §6Fuel Cell§r is connected to the §9Heat Sink§r "network", so they all recive enough cooling.

2. Any §9Heat Sinks§r that are not connected by a face to another §9Heat Sink§r will not be active. This can be bypassed by using a §7Conductor§r to connect valid §9Heat Sinks§r.

3. Active §bModerator Blocks§r are those directly adjacent to a §6Fuel Cell§r.



If building a reactor for power, you'll want to match the heat as close as possible to prevent loss of Steam.

This quest will help you understand how to process §dIrradiator§r recipes.

After each §6Fuel Cell§r is receving enough §aFlux Factor§r to activate, you can create additional §bModerator Lines§r extending out from your §6Fuel Cells§r capped by an §dIrradiator§r. 

Adding up the total §aFlux Factor§r in the §bModerator Line§r between the §6Cell§r and §dIrradiator§r will give us the amount of Radiaton per tick used in processing recipes such as §7N-Type Doped Silicon§r.


Remember, each §bModerator Line§r extending from a §6Cell§r will increase the §eHeat§r.
